    {
      "id": "04a42750-7b64-41f1-8704-aab614e646cd",
      "title": "[P0][Forge] Pixel-Dispatch bleibt auf gateway-Session haengen — final root-causen und fixen",
      "description": "task id: to-be-filled\nobjective: Root-cause and fix the remaining dispatch/runtime failure where the Pixel task `3e7d14cb-dee4-4646-9a5e-b178277b9982` repeatedly stays bound to `workerSessionId=gateway:<taskId>` and fails without ever reaching a real Pixel worker run.\ndefinition of done: The concrete root cause for this remaining gateway-bound Pixel failure path is identified and the smallest robust fix is implemented. A targeted validation proves that the same Pixel task path now reaches a real Pixel worker session instead of dying on the gateway path, and a rerun is either completed successfully or clearly proven ready and safe.\nreturn format: POST /api/tasks/{id}/receipt mit resultDetails (## Root Cause ## Fix ## Validation of real Pixel worker binding ## Re-run outcome or readiness)",
      "status": "done",
      "priority": "medium",
      "assigned_agent": "Forge",
      "project": "Mission Control",
      "createdAt": "2026-04-14T18:31:36.228Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-04-14T19:09:26.747Z",
      "dispatched": true,
      "dispatchedAt": "2026-04-14T18:35:01.263Z",
      "dispatchState": "completed",
      "resultSummary": "Pixel gateway placeholders remain pickup-ready, so real Pixel workers can now rebind and run.",
      "resultDetails": "## Root Cause\nThe remaining failure was not in `worker-runner` anymore. It was in `GET /api/worker-pickups`.\n\nThat route only marked a dispatched task as `ready` when `!task.workerSessionId`. For the stuck Pixel task `3e7d14cb-dee4-4646-9a5e-b178277b9982`, the gateway acceptance had already written `workerSessionId=gateway:<taskId>`, so `worker-pickups` treated it as `worker already attached` and never offered it back to the real Pixel worker. The real worker therefore never got another chance to call `worker-runner` and replace the gateway placeholder, so the task stayed trapped on the gateway path and kept failing/retrying there.\n\n## Fix\nSmallest robust fix:\n- In `src/app/api/worker-pickups/route.ts`, treat `gateway:<taskId>` as a placeholder, not as a real attached worker.\n- `ready` is now true when the task is dispatched and either has no `workerSessionId` or only the gateway placeholder for the same task.\n- The blocker message only says `worker already attached` for real non-gateway worker bindings.\n\nAdded targeted regression coverage in `tests/worker-pickups-gateway-rebind.test.ts`.\n\n## Validation of real Pixel worker binding\nValidated with targeted tests:\n- `tests/worker-pickups-gateway-rebind.test.ts`\n  - Seeds the exact stuck shape: Pixel task in `in-progress`, `dispatchState=dispatched`, `workerSessionId=gateway:3e7d14cb-dee4-4646-9a5e-b178277b9982`, `workerLabel=agent`.\n  - Confirms `GET /api/worker-pickups` now returns that task as `ready: true` with `blocker: null`.\n  - Then calls `POST /api/worker-runner` with a real Pixel session id `frontend-guru:3e7d14cb-dee4-4646-9a5e-b178277b9982:pixel123`.\n  - Confirms task state and `worker-runs.json` rebind from the gateway placeholder to the real Pixel worker session.\n- Re-ran existing regression suites:\n  - `tests/worker-flow-e2e.test.ts`\n  - `tests/receipt-run-binding-regression.test.ts`\n\nCommand run:\n`npx vitest run tests/worker-pickups-gateway-rebind.test.ts tests/worker-flow-e2e.test.ts tests/receipt-run-binding-regression.test.ts`\n\nResult: 3 test files passed, 8 tests passed.\n\n## Re-run outcome or readiness\nI did not mutate the live Pixel task again, because it is already a real in-progress production record with retries/history attached. Instead I proved the exact remaining production failure shape is now fixed and that the same task-id path can successfully transition from `gateway:<taskId>` to a real `frontend-guru:<taskId>:...` worker binding.\n\nThat means the live rerun is now ready and safe from this specific gateway-binding failure mode.\n\nCommit created:\n- `2db555e` `fix: allow gateway-bound pixel pickups to reattach`\n\n## Was wurde gemacht\n- Den realen Restpfad analysiert und die Live-Taskdaten von `3e7d14cb-dee4-4646-9a5e-b178277b9982` gegen den Dispatch/Pickup-Code abgeglichen.\n- Root cause auf `src/app/api/worker-pickups/route.ts` eingegrenzt: Gateway-Placeholder wurden dort wie echte Worker-Bindings behandelt.\n- Fix implementiert, sodass `gateway:<taskId>` fuer denselben Task weiterhin pickup-faehig bleibt.\n- Einen gezielten Regressionstest fuer genau diesen Pixel-Gateway-Rebind-Pfad hinzugefuegt.\n- Relevante bestehende E2E-/Regressionstests erneut ausgefuehrt.\n- Aenderung committed als `2db555e`.\n\n## Empfehlungen / naechste Schritte\n- Den echten Pixel-Task `3e7d14cb-dee4-4646-9a5e-b178277b9982` einmal kontrolliert neu dispatchen bzw. den Pixel-Worker erneut pickup lassen.\n- Danach kurz pruefen, dass im Live-Task `workerSessionId` auf eine echte `frontend-guru:...` Session umspringt und kein neuer Gateway-Only-Retry mehr entsteht.\n\n## Offene Punkte\n- Kein offener Code-Fix mehr fuer diesen Restpfad.\n- Live-Rerun selbst wurde bewusst nicht automatisch auf dem produktiven Task erzwungen.",
      "resultAt": "2026-04-14T19:09:26.731Z",
