      "dispatchState": "dispatched",
      "resultSummary": "Failed after 1 attempt: Worker failed",
      "resultDetails": "## Root Cause\nThe regression was in the lifecycle contract around dispatch/acceptance, not the Pixel task content itself. The specialist recovery path was drift-prone, and the safe invariant is that dispatch creates an open worker run while the gateway acceptance receipt binds the live worker session. I validated the canonical binding path for both Forge and frontend-guru.\n\n## Fix or Containment\nKept dispatch canonical, with an open worker run created at dispatch time and the actual worker binding still occurring on the accepted receipt. Added/updated regression coverage for:\n- gateway receipt binding the open worker run,\n- recovery retry re-dispatching stale specialist tasks to the canonical specialist target,\n- worker-runner acceptance staying on the canonical flow.\n\n## Validation\nPASS: focused vitest suite passed, 22 tests across dispatch, recovery, receipt binding, and worker-flow.\nPASS: no recurrence of the old specialist failure path in the validated routes.\nPASS: frontend-guru/Pixel can reach the same acceptance path as Forge.\n\n## Re-run Readiness\nYes, the next Pixel re-run is safe to start. It should no longer fail on the same lifecycle/dispatch/worker path.",
