    {
      "id": "e7e256a7-7bb0-4d14-b38a-6c9cf31ed825",
      "title": "[Nightly] Harden execution-report API route with fail-soft error handling",
      "description": "task id: e7e256a7-7bb0-4d14-b38a-6c9cf31ed825\nobjective: Add a tight top-level fail-soft guard to `mission-control/src/app/api/execution-report/route.ts` so task-store read/parsing or unexpected runtime errors cannot crash the execution-report endpoint. Return structured JSON 500 with a concise error summary, preserve current 400/404 behavior for expected cases, and keep the scope to this route (plus a tiny shared helper only if truly needed).\ndefinition of done: npx tsc --noEmit läuft ohne Fehler. Die Änderung ist live in MC. Keine Regression in bestehenden Routen.\nreturn format: POST http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/tasks/e7e256a7-7bb0-4d14-b38a-6c9cf31ed825/receipt mit Headers x-actor-kind: automation, x-request-class: system und Body: {\"stage\":\"result\",\"resultSummary\":\"<1 Satz>\",\"resultDetails\":\"## Was implementiert\\n<details>\\n## Validierung\\n<tsc-Ergebnis + manuelle Checks>\\n## Impact\\n<was ist jetzt besser>\"}\n\nKontext:\n- Nightly Step 0 scanned all 6 required sources.\n- Source 1 shows fresh cron instability today (`daily-cost-report` timed out once), so resilient reporting surfaces matter.\n- Source 2 had no higher-value stale board hygiene candidate.\n- Source 3 still has broad TS debt and `ignoreBuildErrors: true`, but that is a wider/riskier slice.\n- Source 4 config hygiene is out of bounds tonight (no config edits).\n- Source 5 large files exist but do not beat route hardening on direct stability impact.\n- Source 6 found `src/app/api/execution-report/route.ts` still has no top-level try/catch.\n- This route is central for automated execution reporting: it reads taskboard state and formats operator-facing output. A fail-soft wrapper is a small, safe slice with immediate stability benefit and avoids repeating the recent live-agents hardening target.",
