    {
      "id": "15e8959d-8110-4594-b8dc-4b23adb12236",
      "title": "Investigate root cause of persistent timeouts",
      "description": "task id: 15e8959d-8110-4594-b8dc-4b23adb12236\nobjective: Investigate the current root cause of persistent timeouts across the affected cron/productive flows and identify the smallest robust fix path or containment so productive automatic work is not delayed by repeated timeout failures.\ndefinition of done: The affected timeout family is classified with concrete root cause or top suspect path, and either a fix or a safe containment is implemented and validated. The result must clearly state whether this remains a blocker for productive auto-dispatch.\nreturn format: POST /api/tasks/15e8959d-8110-4594-b8dc-4b23adb12236/receipt mit resultDetails (## Scope ## Root Cause ## Fix or Containment ## Validation ## Blocking Assessment)",
      "status": "failed",
      "priority": "medium",
      "assigned_agent": "Forge",
      "project": "Mission Control",
      "createdAt": "2026-04-12T04:59:03.326Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-04-14T19:45:08.862Z",
      "dispatched": true,
      "dispatchedAt": "2026-04-14T19:45:08.598Z",
      "dispatchState": "dispatched",
      "dispatchTarget": "sre-expert",
      "resultSummary": "Failed after 3 attempts: Worker failed",
      "resultDetails": "## Was wurde gemacht\n- Root-cause analysis in `mission-control` focused on the dispatch -> pickup -> worker-runner path behind repeated timeout/Worker failed behavior in productive automatic flows.\n- Confirmed the shared failure family: `dispatchTask(...)` wrote `workerSessionId` onto freshly dispatched tasks before any worker actually accepted them.\n- Verified that this made `GET /api/worker-pickups` classify new dispatched work as blocked (`worker already attached`) and made `POST /api/worker-runner` reject the same tasks with `409 worker already attached`.\n- Implemented the smallest robust fix in `src/lib/task-dispatch.ts`: dispatch now keeps the worker run record, but does **not** pre-bind `task.workerSessionId` before acceptance.\n- Updated regression expectations in `tests/task-dispatch-canonical.test.ts`.\n- Added an end-to-end regression in `tests/worker-flow-e2e.test.ts` proving that a freshly dispatched task can now be accepted by `worker-runner` and moved to `receiptStage=accepted` with a real gateway session id.\n- Committed the fix as `082870d fix: avoid phantom worker attachment on dispatch`.\n\n## Empfehlungen / naechste Schritte\n- Deploy/restart Mission Control with commit `082870d` so new productive dispatches stop entering the false-attached-worker path.\n- After deploy, watch `/api/worker-pickups` and recent task receipts once to confirm ready tasks become accepted instead of timing out.\n- Optional follow-up: add one route-level regression around `/api/worker-pickups` readiness to make the blockage visible even earlier.\n\n## Offene Punkte\n- Existing historical failed/timeouted tasks remain historical artifacts until retried or re-dispatched; the fix prevents new occurrences but does not silently rewrite old board history.",
